File: MTN will be reducing its data prices on Friday. JOHANNESBURG - MTN will be reducing its data prices on Friday. This comes after the telecoms giant reached a deal with the Competition Commission. Last year, the commission announced data prices from the country's mobile networks are overpriced. WATCH: MTN makes announcement on data MTN customers can now expect to R99 for 1 GB of data per month. Users will also be able to manage their data use at no additional cost, through the company's website.